Product name: Leather Luggage Tag Personalized, Leather Luggage Tag, Leather Luggage Tags, Luggage Tag, Custom Luggage Tag, Engraved Luggage Tag,
Description:
Craig Wesley & I travel internationally about twice a year and the most stressful part of the trip is usually before we even leave. We have an adorable trouble making basset hound that we have to drop-off at the dog boarders, we come back home to lock all the doors and grab our luggage, check the traffic to see if we need to leave earlier than planned, check a zillion times if we have our passports, and this is all before we even get to the airport. Of course, what's the most stressful part once you're in line to check-in for your flight? Having to find a pen and filing out an luggage tag that always seems to get smudge marks. 
Traveling is stressful enough, why not make it just a little bit easier by having your own personalized leather luggage tag.
Our Leather Luggage Tag is handmade in the San Francisco Bay Area with your choice of American Made Wickett & Craig "English" Bridle Vegetable Tanned Leather, the same leather Louis Vuitton uses for straps, or Natural Vegetable Tanned Leather. Each tag is finished off with a simple eyelet and your choice of steel wire keychain or beaded keychain.
Measures 4 inches X 2.5 inches X 0.07 inches thick, excluding key chain.
HOW TO ORDER
Please leave your details in the note during checkout. 
Please note that our system does not support special characters in foreign language such as ñ í ë. Please provide the information in English only. 
This is made to order listing. Please allow 1-3 business days before we ship it out.
Thank you
WHY VEGETABLE TANNED LEATHER:
Vegetable tanned leather is cow leather tanned with using tannins and other ingredients found in vegetable matter, such as tree barks prepared in bark mills, woods, leaves, fruits and roots.
Vegetable-tanning is a true Chromium-free method, and does not have harmful chemicals. 
Vegetable tanned leather is the best choice for your health and environment.

Description:
Wonderful antique croquet set in the original wooden box. This great 6 player set is circa late 1800's to early 1900's and is complete with all mallets, balls, wickets, etc. It comes in the original wooden box that has amazing beautiful old fashioned graphics with the maker, Hibbard (Hibbard, Spencer, Bartlett & Co.), in large stenciled letters on one side. Product name: Hermes Scarf: Washington's Carriage
Description:
This gorgeous Hermes silk scarf, Washington's Carriage, is in a very patriotic colorway of red, white, blue, gold and beige. Designed by Caty Latham, the scarf depicts the carriage newly-inaugurated George Washington rode in 1789 from Federal Hall, his New York residence, to the Federation's new capital on the banks of the Potomac River.
From Hermes: "The crowds were ecstatic, and the presidential escort was a fine spectacle indeed. Three years later, in 1792, a watercolour signed by J. Robert Hart gave a carriage-painter’s view of the carriage of George Washington, made in London. The painting is the inspiration for this carré. We like to think that the first presidential carriage, the focal point of that historic day, looked every bit like the one shown here."
Excellent vintage condition, 35" square, with no stains, snags or runs, and care tag attached.

Description:
You will receive 18 VARIOUS Fizzy Bath Bombs
Grab a great lot size of various fizzy bath bombs. You will get 18 "mini" fizzy bath bombs. Each bath bomb is about 2.0 ounces, about the size of a golf ball, and is big enough to make your bath a little more spa like. These could also be great gifts or even party favors. 
So, what exactly is a bath bomb? 
Our bath bomb is a hard, round ball that when dropped into your bath tub, begins to fizz. While the fizzing is occurring, the bath bomb begins to release its premium fragrance and moisturizing oils. Also being released are the muscle relaxing Epsom salts. Now all you need to do is sit back, relax, and enjoy.

Product name: Essentials* 3.0 Bullet Journal Stencil, Filofax, Midori Traveler's Notebook, Hobonichi, Erin Condren Planner
Description:
* * UPDATED 2017 DESIGN * *
A newly calibrated machine, new blades, and a new, sleeker design means this year's bullets are smaller than ever! Check out the photos to see the new sizes and shapes. Almost ALL bullets now fit inside a Leuchtturm1917 dotted box. Huzzah!
----------
This listing is for a handmade stencil designed by Moo and the Boo. 
The icons on this stencil were specifically designed small enough to fit on a single line or within a single dotted box for use as bullets for the bullet journal system. Most thick, rigid stencils you find in stores have large icons that will not fit inside a bullet box. I tried many store-bought stencils but could never find icons small enough to suit my needs. So I decided to make my own.
To maintain the smallest shape possible, tiny bullet icons must be cut on thin stencil film to allow room for the tip of a pen. These stencils are made on 7.5 mil Mylar film. Although this makes the stencil much thinner than most are used to, be assured the stencil is very durable and will not rip or tear. It is super lightweight so not to add bulk to your journal, flexible, and partially opaque so you can position it correctly on your page. 
Tips for best results:
It may take some time getting used to using a thin, flexible stencil because it conforms to your surface, but it gets easier the more you practice, I promise! 
Use a gentle pen stroke with the stencil as your guide for best results. Press the stencil firmly to the page with your hand if you would like to use more pressure with your pen tip. 
This stencil was also designed to fit in the back pocket of most journals like Leuchtturm and Moleskine (4x7 inches). You can also attach your stencil inside your journal with Washi tape. 
Included are weather icons, banners, and other flourishes to be used as page embellishments. These are much larger than the bullet icons and are not intended to be used as bullets. 
Our stencils work best with fine tipped pens like Micron 01, Sharpie pens, or Staedtler Fineliners. Straight tipped pens and pencils (like Bic mechanical pencils) are best suited. Tapered pens like ballpoints and blunt pencils may not work as well with the tiny, bullet-sized icons. Heavy-inking pens may cause bleeding under the stencil, so I like to use the Micron pens, mechanical pencils, or the Sharpie fine point, no-bleed pens. Don't be afraid to touch up the icon using freehand to get it just right. 
Dimensions: 4"x7"
Examples of how I use some of the icons:
- 8 water drops for tracking my water intake
- row of squares for tracking goal progress
- envelope for email and other correspondence
- pushpin for saving ideas to Pinterest
- facebook and twitter icons for post reminders
- wine glass for date night
- apple for meal planning
- coffee cup for morning routines and coffee dates
- barbell for working out
- airplane for travel
- dollar sign for financial responsibilities
You can also mix and match the icons to build more complex images. The possibilities are endless!
* This order is for the stencil only. Journal and pens not included. 
** Handmade stencils aren't for everyone. If for any reason you are unhappy with your purchase, you may send it back for a full product refund. Stencil must be in new condition and returned within 30 days of delivery date.

Product name: One Gallon Mead Making Kit With Fresh Local California Raw Honey
Description:
Mead or honey wine is one of the oldest alcoholic drinks known to man. It is made from honey and water! It may be still, carbonated, or sparkling; it may be dry, semi-sweet, or sweet.
 Mead is independently multicultural. It is known from many sources of ancient history throughout Europe, Africa and Asia, although archaeological evidence of it is ambiguous. Its origins are lost in prehistory; "it can be regarded as the ancestor of all fermented drinks," Maguelonne Toussaint-Samat has observed, "antedating the cultivation of the soil." Claude Levi-Strauss makes a case for the invention of mead as a marker of the passage "from nature to culture."
Your Mead Kit will guide you through the ancient art of making this wonderfully delicious alcoholic drink in as little as 3 weeks!
Your Kit includes:
Ingredients
1 lb of Fresh California raw honey
1 pkg of yeast for Mead Making
1 pkg of sterilizing agent for disinfecting and treating the mead
Oak or Fruit Flavoring
Equipment
1 Gal.  Glass Fermentation and Bottling Jug
Siphon Tubing
AirLock
Airlock screw cap
Metal screw cap
Instructions and Mead Making Booklet
